  "text": "Another use for punctuations is to declare information about the arriving data, rather than the data that has been seen. For example, Fegaras et al. [CITATION_1] use annotations in the data stream to declare the incoming data structure, and whether the data fragment following the annotation is a repeat or an update. One could pursue this direction further to specify other constraints, such as a sort order over particular attributes or even attribute domains.",
